commit_message:
Register JSON-Home data for resources actions

Some resources have many actions registered with them as controller extensions.
For example 'servers' has lot of actions with it - lock/unlock etc
This patch adds support to register json-home data for resources
actions.

json-home data for resources action will looks like-
{
    "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/rel/servers/lock": {
      "href-template": "/v2.1/{project_id}/servers/{server_id}/action",
      "href-vars": {
        "project_id": "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/param/project_id",
        "server_id": "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/param/server_id"
      }
    },
    "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/rel/servers/unlock": {
      "href-template": "/v2.1/{project_id}/servers/{server_id}/action",
      "href-vars": {
        "project_id": "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/param/project_id",
        "server_id": "http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-compute/2.1/param/server_id"
      }
    },
    ..
}

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-json-home

Change-Id: I628fe2789ed16b314151c5b0d6e6d3998f13fad3

